## Technical Updates
- Added SQLite database for conversation storage
- Created new API endpoints: `/api/conversations`, `/api/conversations/search`, `/api/conversations/save`
- Updated chat interface to automatically save messages
- Added history page with search capabilities
- Implemented E2E tests with Cucumber
- Updated CSS for responsive design
# Change Log - Individual Iteration

## Feature 1: Optional 3-LLM Response Mode (Story Points: 4)
- **Description**: Logged-in users can choose whether one LLM or three LLMs should respond to a prompt
- **Implementation**: Added a "Have 3 LLMs respond" checkbox on the chat page and updated the frontend request flow to send the useThreeLLM flag to the backend
- **PR Links**: [Individual iteration work on Yang-Chen branch]
- **Status**: Completed

## Feature 2: Responses from 3 LLMs with Best Answer Highlighting (Story Points: 5)
- **Description**: When 3-LLM mode is enabled, users receive three responses and one best answer is highlighted for easier comparison
- **Implementation**: Updated the backend to generate three responses, added judge logic to select the best answer, saved 3-LLM messages in the existing schema, and updated the frontend to display the grouped responses with highlighted best answer
- **PR Links**: [Individual iteration work on Yang-Chen branch]
- **Status**: Completed

## Feature 3: Search and Filter Conversations with 3-LLM Responses (Story Points: 3)
- **Description**: Returning users can identify and filter conversations created with 3-LLM mode
- **Implementation**: Added a [3LLM] title prefix for 3-LLM conversations and added a history-page filter to show only 3-LLM conversations without changing the database schema
- **PR Links**: [Individual iteration work on Yang-Chen branch]
- **Status**: Completed

## Technical Updates
- Added helper logic for 3-LLM model selection, judge prompt construction, judge result parsing, and fallback best-answer selection
- Added backend unit tests for 3-LLM helper logic using Jasmine
- Added acceptance test scenarios for 3-LLM workflow using Cucumber and Puppeteer
- Updated homepage behavior so users start a conversation from the landing page and continue it in the dedicated conversation page
- Improved empty-state messaging and page layout to better support the new 3-LLM workflow
